<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910830-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>910830-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Applied Solar Energy Corp.:   Westar Capital to Acquire   Firm for Up to $25 Million</HL><DATE>08/30/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   ACY SOLR</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Applied Solar Energy Corp. said it agreed to be acquiredby Westar Capital in a transaction valued by both companiesat &quot;between $20 million and $25 million.&quot;   Applied Solar, based in City of Industry, Calif., saidthat under the agreement, American Cyanamid Co., which owns73% of Applied Solar's stock, would receive &quot;the equivalentof $3.58 per share plus cash and notes in payment&quot; of about$8.5 million of loans outstanding. Other shareholders wouldreceive $6 a share in cash.</LP><TEXT>   A spokesman for American Cyanamid, based in Wayne, N.J.,declined to elaborate on the agreement.   Westar Capital is a Costa Mesa, Calif.-based investmentconcern. Applied Solar Energy makes solar cells and otherphotosensor and laser products. American Cyanamid is abiotechnology and chemical concern.   Applied Solar said it plans to retain an investment bankerto provide a &quot;fairness opinion&quot; on the agreement, which isalso subject to other conditions and approvals.</TEXT></DOC>